WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:11.996
Two motions, two different stories. Let's learn to read vote results like a seasoned
board secretary.

00:12.296 --> 00:22.578
Every motion card carries a tally bar — green for For, red for Against, gray for Abstain
— and under it, each director's vote, by name.

00:22.878 --> 00:30.904
The math is simple majority. Seven directors sit on this board, so four For votes carry
any motion.

00:31.204 --> 00:43.982
The festival motion counted five For, one Against. That's a majority — the card says
Passed, in green. The decision is final, and this card is the record of it.

00:44.282 --> 00:56.412
The bank account motion sits at three For, one Against. No result badge yet — it's still
open, waiting on three directors. You can already see it leaning.

00:56.712 --> 01:09.082
And when a passed vote needs a paper trail, the Board Action and Vote document in your
library turns it into a signed record. Next: keeping every board date straight, with the
Calendar.
